  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AssetSetter
    The AssetSetter class is responsible for initializing and placing game objects and zombies within the game world.
    CollisionChecker
    The CollisionChecker class is responsible for detecting and managing collisions between entities and tiles or objects within the game world.
    EventHandler
    The EventHandler class is responsible for managing events that occur within the game.
    EventRect
    EventRect extends the Rectangle class to include functionality for in-game events.
    GamePanel
    The GamePanel class serves as the main controller for the game.
    KeyHandler
    The KeyHandler class implements the KeyListener interface and handles all keyboard interactions for controlling the game state and player movement.
    Main
    The Main class serves as the entry point for the game application.
    Sound
    The Sound class is responsible for loading and playing sound files.
    UI
    The UI class is responsible for rendering the game's user interface, including the HUD (Heads-Up Display), title screen, pause screen, settings screen, and game over screen.
    UtilityTool
    The UtilityTool class provides utility functions to manipulate images.
